This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

1:43 PM/RM 301. Defendant Stacy A. Stutts in court.  Attorney Kelly Hays in court for State of Wisconsin, via zoom. Court reviews case history. Court notes Information had not been filed. State has efiled information and tracks criminal complaint. Court questions Def. regarding plea. Def. would like counsel. Court advises Def. to contact PD Office immediately. Information will be filed in a timely matter. Bond continues.
Status hearing scheduled for November 14, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

2:32 PM Room 203 Defendant Stacy A. Stutts appeared by video. Attorney Elizabeth R. Gebert appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. All parties via Zoom. Court calls case and reviews. Court notes that right for an attorney has been waived by defendant prior to hearing. Defendant agrees and waives right for an attorney. The Court questions Ms. Stutts. The State is satisfied and the Court finds that it is appropriate. The defendant waives a preliminary examination. The Court accepts waiver preliminary examination and finds probable cause and binds over. DA makes statement. An arraignment on October 17, 2022 at 1:30PM is scheduled. Court recess at 2:39 PM.
Arraignment scheduled for October 17, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

4:14 PM Defendant Stacy A. Stutts appeared by video, in custody in Langlade County Jail.  Prosecuting attorney Kelly L Hays in court for the State of Wisconsin, via zoom.  Court reviews case history. Def. does not wish for an attorney. Victim is present in courtroom. State is in compliance with victim rights.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for September 27, 2022 at 02:30 pm.

No illegal use or possession of controlled substances.
No contact with Crab N Jacks.
Surrender passport to Langlade County Sheriff Department.
Not to leave State of Wisconsin

1:09 PM Defendant Stacy A. Stutts appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Elizabeth R. Gebert in court for State of Wisconsin. Room 201. All parties via zoom. Def. has copy of complaint, advised of charges and penalties.  Def. given atty rights and given 3 options, PD, hire own or court appointed atty. State gives bail/bond recommendation and gives conditions No illegal use or possession of controlled substances, No contact with Crab N Jacks, Surrender passport, Not to leave State of Wisconsin. Defendant makes statement on bond. Court orders $6,000 cash bond with conditions No illegal use or possession of controlled substances, No contact with Crab N Jacks, Surrender passport to Langlade County Sheriff Department, Not to leave State of Wisconsin and def. may have bond revisited at later date.
